header.gameNote: SUN BELT CONFERENCE MEN'S CHAMPIONSHIP - QUARTERFINAL

article.description: Shawn Long hit 5 of 6 from long distance and finished with a career-high 34 points to lead Louisiana Lafayette to a 90-68 win over South Alabama in the quarterfinals of the Sun Belt Conference to
article.headline: Louisiana Lafayette pulls away from South Alabama 90-68
article.linkText: Louisiana Lafayette pulls away from South Alabama 90-68
article.story: NEW ORLEANS -- Shawn Long hit 5 of 6 from long distance and finished with a career-high 34 points to lead Louisiana Lafayette to a 90-68 win over South Alabama in the quarterfinals of the Sun Belt Conference tournament on Friday. Johnathan Stove had 14 points, Bryce Washington 12 and Devonta Walker 11 for the fourth-seeded Ragin' Cajuns (17-13), who meet top-seeded Arkansas-Little Rock in the semifinals on Saturday. Stove and Hayward Register hit 3-pointers before Long had back-to-back baskets to close a 12-0 run that put Louisiana Lafayette up 24-12 midway through the first half. The Ragin' Cajuns led 51-37 at the break. The Jaguars (14-19) got within 10 early in the second half before Louisiana Lafayette pulled away. Washington made it a 20-point game with 13:54 to go. Barrington Stevens led South Alabama with 13 points.
